<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<knowl mode="exercise" xmlns="https://spatext.clontz.org" version="0.2">
    <!-- {{#sinusoids}} -->
    <knowl>
        <!-- {{#findfunction}} -->
        <content>
            <p>
For the pictured function below, determine a formula in the form 
<m>f(t) = a \sin(k(t-b))+c</m> or <m> g(t) = a \cos(k(t-b))+c</m> 
that fits the data. Write 1-2 sentences to explain your thinking, 
referencing the function's amplitude, midline, and period, 
as well as any horizontal shift you use. If a point looks like it is
on the midline or a minimum or maximum of the function, 
you can assume that it is.
            </p>
            <p>
                <image
                    source="assets/C2/generated/{{__seed__}}/{{filename}}.png" />
                    <!-- description="Line with intercept {{intercept}} and slope {{slope}}."/> -->
            </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p><m>y={{line}}</m></p>
        </outtro>
        <!-- {{/findfunction}} -->
        <!-- {{#findfeatures}} -->
        <content>
            <p>Consider the function <m>k(t)={{sinusoid}}</m>.
            State the function's exact <b>amplitude</b>, 
            <b>midline</b> (<m>y=c</m>),
            <b>range</b>,
            and <b>period</b> (<m>P</m>). </p>
        </content>
        <outtro>
            <p>
                <list>
                    <item>Amplitude: {{amplitude}}</item>
                    <item>Midline: {{midline}}</item>
                    <item>Range: <m>{{midline}} \pm {{amplitude}}</m></item>
                    <item>Period: <m>{{period}}</m></item>
                </list>
            </p>
        </outtro>
        <!-- {{/findfeatures}} -->
    </knowl>
    <!-- {{/sinusoids}} -->
</knowl>